<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-31T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-31T14:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/1302a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-31T14:00:00-05:00">October
                                    31, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>66. In connection with our study of Peruvian requests for short-term
                            credits, please inform the Department by telegraph regarding the
                            following points: <pb facs="0791" n="783" xml:id="pg_783"/>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Most recent position of the Central Bank, including, gold,
                                    foreign exchange, banking rediscounts, credits to Government,
                                    note circulation, and deposits. (The most recent statement
                                    available here is that of June 30.)</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>Statistics since June of imports and exports.</item>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>What volume of transfer of interest and dividends is taking
                                    place? Capital movement?</item>
                                <label>4.</label>
                                <item>Has any back-log of commercial exchange accumulated?</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>